<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Start an FTC Team - FTC Starter Hub</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/main.css?v=17">
</head>
<body>
  <header></header>

  <main class="start-team-page">
    <div class="container start-team-shell">
      <a href="/" class="btn btn-secondary back-button">&larr; Back Home</a>

      <section class="start-team-hero">
        <div class="start-team-hero-copy">
          <p class="hero-label">Launch guide</p>
          <h1>Start an FTC team with a real plan, not guesswork.</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">
            We’ve turned the setup process into a simple path: get a sponsor, gather students, lock in support,
            and move toward your first competition with confidence.
          </p>

          <div class="cta-buttons start-team-actions">
            <a href="/team-register" class="btn btn-primary">Register recruiting status</a>
            <a href="/resources" class="btn btn-secondary">Browse resources</a>
            <a href="/teams-nearby" class="btn btn-secondary">See active teams</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="start-team-summary-card">
          <p class="summary-kicker">What this page gives you</p>
          <div class="summary-metrics">
            <div class="summary-metric">
              <strong>9</strong>
              <span>guided setup steps</span>
            </div>
                        <div class="summary-metric">
              <strong>3</strong>
              <span>launch priorities</span>
            </div>
            <div class="summary-metric">
              <strong>All-in-one</strong>
              <span>team checklist</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="summary-note">
            Use the roadmap below to decide what needs to happen first, what can wait, and how to keep the team moving.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section start-team-overview">
        <h2>Before you open step 1</h2>
        <div class="overview-grid">
          <div class="overview-card">
            <h3>Build visibility fast</h3>
            <p>Once you are recruiting, register the team so students can actually find and contact you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section start-team-roadmap">
        <h2>Setup roadmap</h2>
        <p class="roadmap-intro">
          Each step includes a focused topic and a short explanation so you can keep momentum without getting lost.
        </p>

        <div class="step-grid start-team-step-grid">
          <a href="/start-team-step1" class="btn btn-secondary step-card roadmap-card">
            <strong>Step 1 · Foundation</strong>
            <span>Sponsor organization</span>
            <p>Secure the school, club, or nonprofit that will host the team.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/start-team-step2" class="btn btn-secondary step-card roadmap-card">
            <strong>Step 2 · FIRST setup</strong>
            <span>Get FIRST involved</span>
            <p>Confirm registrations, program details, and the official path forward.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/start-team-step3" class="btn btn-secondary step-card roadmap-card">
            <strong>Step 3 · People</strong>
            <span>Recruit students</span>
            <p>Find the students who will build, code, design, and lead the team.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/start-team-step4" class="btn btn-secondary step-card roadmap-card">
            <strong>Step 4 · Leadership</strong>
            <span>Coach or mentor</span>
            <p>Bring in adult support to guide the team and keep it sustainable.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/start-team-step5" class="btn btn-secondary step-card roadmap-card">
            <strong>Step 5 · Money</strong>
            <span>Funding plan</span>
            <p>Outline costs, sponsorship ideas, and a realistic budget target.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/start-team-step6" class="btn btn-secondary step-card roadmap-card">
            <strong>Step 6 · Space</strong>
            <span>Workspace setup</span>
            <p>Make sure the team has a place to meet, build, and store materials.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/start-team-step7" class="btn btn-secondary step-card roadmap-card">
            <strong>Step 7 · Hardware</strong>
            <span>Equipment and parts</span>
            <p>Identify the tools, kits, and components you need to start building.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/start-team-step8" class="btn btn-secondary step-card roadmap-card">
            <strong>Step 8 · Skills</strong>
            <span>Learn and prepare</span>
            <p>Begin programming, mechanical practice, and routine team training.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/start-team-step9" class="btn btn-secondary step-card roadmap-card">
            <strong>Step 9 · Competition</strong>
            <span>First event prep</span>
            <p>Use a checklist so your first competition feels organized instead of rushed.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section start-team-next">
        <h2>How to keep momentum</h2>
        <div class="next-steps-grid">
          <div class="next-step-card">
            <h3>Start with a short kickoff meeting</h3>
            <p>Pick the sponsor, mentor, and student core before trying to solve every detail at once.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="next-step-card">
            <h3>Track decisions in one place</h3>
            <p>Use a shared doc or notebook so team roles, deadlines, and contacts stay visible.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="next-step-card">
            <h3>Keep recruiting visible</h3>
            <p>As soon as the team is ready, register your status so interested students can find you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section start-team-footer">
        <div class="important-box">
          <h2>Ready for the next move?</h2>
          <p>
            If you already know your team is recruiting, jump straight to registration. If not, open step 1 and work
            through the roadmap in order.
          </p>
          <div class="cta-buttons">
            <a href="/team-register" class="btn btn-primary">Register Your Team</a>
            <a href="/start-team-step1" class="btn btn-secondary">Begin Step 1</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <script src="/assets/js/main.js?v=9"></script>
</body>
</html>


